cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language models and natural language processing. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes the use of federated learning, a machine learning technique. Additionally, it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with intelligent systems for language processing. It may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses privacy-sensitive data and training models without sensitive data leaving the devices. Finally, it may fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it proposes algorithms for efficient finite state transducer conversion.
